@generic{Varanda2020,
   abstract = {Overview of LT: Born after debating the UN Mission for the Central African Republic with Portuguese Special Forces officers, project “ORÁCULO” tackles the challenge of achieving situational awareness with limited resources in a peacekeeping operation. It proposes to combine state-of-the-art text mining algorithms, geodatabases and spatiotemporal pattern mining techniques to develop a system capable of extracting conflict-relevant events from news streams selected by open source analysts, of transforming and loading those events in a geodatabase, and of detecting event patterns with tactical and operational significance. The lightning talk invites the public to step into the shoes of an intelligence officer posted to the UN Peacekeeping Mission for the Central African Republic. It begins by describing the obstacles they face to achieve situational awareness for the peacekeepers they support. It then builds on that description to present the proposed solution, “ORÁCULO”, detailing its inputs, processes and outputs, as well as the increased capabilities that it offers to the intelligence officers and staff. It then concludes by highlighting the development done thus far in the overall project and the way ahead. Goals & Competencies: 1. Compare the challenge of attaining situational awareness in a peacekeeping setting with a symmetric conflict. 2. Explain the role of event extraction techniques and open source intelligence (OSINT) in achieving situational awareness in a peacekeeping setting. 3. Explain the role of spatiotemporal pattern mining techniques in achieving situational awareness in a peacekeeping setting.},
